United States Army)|Shoulder sleeve insignia (SSI)]]''' are cloth emblems worn on the shoulders of US Army uniforms to identify the primary headquarters to which a soldier is assigned. The SSI of some army divisions have become known in popular culture.<ref name=\"DIV\">[http://www.tioh.hqda.pentagon.mil/DUI_SSI_COA_page.htm Distinctive Unit Insignia, Coat of Arms, Shoulder Sleeve Insignia] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060427133645/http://www.tioh.hqda.pentagon.mil/DUI_SSI_COA_page.htm |date=27 April 2006 }}</ref><ref>http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/cbtchron/adcomp.html Component Elements of Armored Divisions</ref><ref>http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/cbtchron/cavcomp.html Component Elements of the 1st Cavalry Divisions</ref>\n\n== Airborne/infantry ==\nNote: several insignia are of World War II formations. {{Clear}}Note: US infantry divisions were not formed under the following numbers:\"53\"; \"54\"; \"56\"; \"57\"; \"58\"; \"60\"; \"64\".<ref>http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/cbtchron/infcomp.html Component Elements of Infantry Divisions</ref><ref>http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/cbtchron/abdcomp.html Component Elements of Airborne Divisions</ref>\n<br>\n<gallery class=\"center\" classes=\"center\">\nFile:Combat service identification badge of the 1st Infantry Division.svg|[[1st Infantry Division (United States)|1st Infantry Division]]{{-}}\"Big Red One\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\">{{cite web | title = Special Designation Listing By Unit Number | date = 1 August 2008 | publisher = [[United States Army Center of Military History]] | url = http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/spdes-123.html | accessdate = 27 October 2008 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080501131728/http://www.history.army.mil/html/forcestruc/spdes-123.html | archivedate = 1 May 2008}}</ref>\nFile:2nd Infantry Division CSIB.png|[[2nd Infantry Division (United States)|2nd Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Indianhead\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:3rd Infantry Division CSIB.png|[[3rd Infantry Division (United States)|3rd Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Marne Division\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:4th Infantry Division CSIB2.svg|[[4th Infantry Division (United States)|4th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Ivy Division\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:US 5th Infantry Division.svg|[[5th Infantry Division (United States)|5th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Red Diamond\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:6th Infantry Division.svg|[[6th Infantry Division (United States)|6th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Sightseeing Sixth\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:USA - 6 ABN DIV.svg|[[6th Airborne Division (United States)|6th Airborne Division]]<br>[[Operation Vendetta (Deception)|Operation Vendetta]] \"phantom\" unit\nFile:7th Infantry Division CSIB.jpg|[[7th Infantry Division (United States)|7th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Bayonet\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:8th Infantry Division patch.svg|[[8th Infantry Division (United States)|8th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Pathfinder\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:9th Infantry Division patch.svg|[[9th Infantry Division (United States)|9th Infantry Division]]{{Clear}}\"Old Reliables\"<ref name=\"cmhlist\"/>\nFile:USA - 9 ABN DIV.svg|[[9th Airborne Division (United States)|9th Airborne Division]]{{Clear}}[[Fourteenth United States Army|Fourteenth Army]] \"phantom\" unit\nFile:WWI10D.svg|[[10th Infantry Division Regular Army (United States)|10th Division]]<br>(Regular Army/National Guard unit of 1918\u201319)\nFile:10th Mountain Division CSIB.jpg|[[10th Mountain Division (United States)|10th Mountain Division]]{{Clear}}\"Climb to Glory\" Division Formerly \"10th Light Division (Alpine)\" [World War II]<br/>10th Infantry Division{{Clear}}June 1948 - June 1958\nFile:WWI11D.svg|[[11th Infantry Division (United States)|11th Infantry Division]]<br>\"Lafayette Div\"<br>(Regular Army/National Guard 1918\u201319; distinct from National Guard 11th Division)\nFile:11th